{
  "message": "test(fcp-crypto): add COSE_Sign1 golden fixtures for multi-kid + multi-op\n\nCapture deterministic COSE_Sign1 capability-token outputs so any\nrefactor of the CBOR/COSE encoding path can be caught byte-for-byte\nagainst a pinned reference instead of re-derived each run.\n\nNew files under crates/fcp-crypto/tests/golden/cose/:\n\n- sign1_single_op_capability.hex \u2014 canonical encoding of a capability\n  token with a single allowed operation.\n- sign1_multi_op_capability.hex \u2014 canonical encoding of a capability\n  token with multiple operations in its allow list, to lock the array\n  ordering and CBOR canonicalization (definite-length, sorted map keys).\n- sign1_multi_kid_seed_{04,05,06}.hex \u2014 three deterministic signing-key\n  seeds producing the same protected-header `kid` \u2192 signature mapping,\n  providing rotating-key regression coverage for verifiers that dispatch\n  on kid.\n\nThese fixtures are consumed by the new golden-vector test module in\ncrates/fcp-crypto (added in a prior commit) and are intentionally\nchecked in as plain hex so that a diff-review of any future regeneration\nis human-readable. Each file is <1KB.",
